### 9. RULES.JSON (Lines 1-168)
**Purpose**: Declarative net request rules for tracker blocking

**Structure**: Array of 15 blocking rules targeting common tracking services

**Key Blocked Services**:
- Google Analytics and Tag Manager
- Facebook tracking pixels
- DoubleClick advertising
- Hotjar analytics
- Mixpanel analytics
- Amplitude analytics
- Segment analytics
- Optimizely A/B testing
- Crazy Egg heatmaps
- FullStory session recording
- Mouseflow analytics
- Microsoft Clarity

**Rule Format**:
- Each rule has unique ID, priority, action (block), and conditions
- Conditions specify URL filters and resource types (script, image, xmlhttprequest)
- Rules block specific tracking domains and services

